news.title: Office leasing to record 70 million sq ft across nine cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The office sector witnessed a gross absorption of 53.8 million sq ft during January to September 2024 across nine cities, recording a 19% year-on-year growth.

news.title: Macrotech Developers reports 21% growth in pre-sales in Q2 FY25
news.para: The company has posted pre-sales of Rs 83 billion in the first half of FY25. The pre-sales growth in the first half of the financial year is 21% year-on-year.

news.title: Boson Whitewater partners with Biome Environmental for indirect potable water reuse project in Bengaluru
news.para: The project produces 6.4 lakhs litres of potable drinking water per day. It is energy-efficient using just 0.25 units of electricity per 1,000 litres.

news.title: NBCC to undertake SIDBI’s Vashi redevelopment project worth Rs 142 crore
news.para: NBCC signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with SIDBI in 2023 which included planning, designing and architectural concept and other services drawings and specifications by SIDBI.

news.title: Union cabinet approves Chennai metro rail project phase-II
news.para: The total length of the metro lines is 118.9 km having 128 stations. The project completion cost is Rs 63,246 crore and is planned to be completed by 2027.

news.title: Hong Kong will not sell commercial land in Q3 FY25
news.para: Development Secretary Bernadette Linn added that the government could miss its target of supplying land to build 13,200 flats in the current financial year ending in March, as it plans to sell just one small residential site this quarter.

news.title: Bengaluru Namma metro's green line extension on Tumakuru Road to open for public soon
news.para: Total length of 77 km within the next few weeks with the 3.1-km extension of the Green Line on Tumakuru Road expected to commence operations this month.

news.title: PM Modi to flag off BKC to Aerey metro section in Maharashtra on October 5
news.para: The PMO said Friday that Modi will inaugurate the Banjara Virasat Museum, celebrating the rich heritage of the Banjara community, in Washim, and launch projects worth Rs 23,300 crore related to the agricultural and animal husbandry sector.

news.title: Delhi civic body clears over 6,156 metric tons of silt and C&D waste from city drains
news.para: "The removed silt and C&D waste are being safely transported to designated dumping sites for proper disposal and bio-remediation. This initial effort to clear the silt from various choked drains is currently in progress," the statement said.

news.title: Madras HC fines sub-registrar Rs 25,000 for refusing to register sale deed
news.para: The court was hearing the petition filed by Pandi, who stated that the Kadambus sub-registrar refused to register his sale deed of a property on the ground that the parent document was not produced.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to allow sand excavation from patta lands
news.para: Taking the reports about shortage of sand in several places across the state with a serious note, principal secretary (mines and geology) Mukesh Kumar Meena reviewed the situation with district collectors and asked them to take all possible measures to ensure smooth supply of stocks.

news.title: Karnataka industrial board to issue notice for acquiring 299 properties
news.para: Under the first package of the project, 299 private properties have been identified for acquisition to facilitate the construction of an elevated corridor from JP Nagar 4th Phase to Mysuru Road

news.title: Noida: YEIDA orders probe against officials for issuing false CCs
news.para: The Authority will also revoke the land allotted to the kiosks in sectors 32, 22D, 20 and 17A under various commercial department schemes. The completion certificates were issued to them between May and July.

news.title: SC dismisses ex-Goa judge’s plea to regain RERA post
news.para: The HC had also directed state govt to appoint retired district judge Vincent M D’Silva in Gauns’s place. The SC bench, comprising the Chief Justice and Justice Manoj Misra, heard Gauns.

news.title: Noida: Homebuyers' association oppose plan to pay full stamp duty during booking
news.para: Buyers expressed concern that their money would get stuck should the builder turned a defaulter and left the project midway. Earlier, buyers paid 10% of the flat cost as the booking amount and made an agreement with the builder on a 100-rupee stamp paper.

news.title: Builder can’t sell properties without basic amenities: Rajasthan HC
news.para: The court directed that urban development & housing department (UDH) must first issue a certificate to the developer or builder confirming whether the residential colony or society is suitable for habitation.

news.title: China's Shimao Group says creditors holding over 50% of debt support its restructuring plan
news.para: Shimao Group said in a filing late on Wednesday the amendments include controlling shareholders committing to not dispose of capital stock to below 20% of total voting power, and certain creditors being paid in mandatory convertible bonds as a fee.

news.title: Institutional investments in real estate rise 45% to $1.15 billion in Q2 FY25: Report
news.para: Among different assets class in the overall real estate market, the consultant noted that office segment attracted USD 616.3 million during the third quarter of this calendar year, a more than seven-fold jump from USD 79.1 million in the year-ago period.

news.title: Furnishka raises Rs 27 crore led by India Quotient
news.para: The new funds will be used to advance product design and development, strengthen manufacturing and supply chain capabilities, and expand to new geographies.
